<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="429" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="429">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="429">
This is a troglophilic species (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/jzs.12201" author="Mammola, S" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Systematics and Evolutionary Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="429" pagination="301 - 316" refId="B12" refString="Mammola, S, Cardoso, P, Ribera, C, Pavlek, M, Isaia, M, 2018. A synthesis on cave-dwelling spiders in Europe. Zoological Systematics and Evolutionary Research 56 (3): 301 - 316, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/jzs.12201" title="A synthesis on cave-dwelling spiders in Europe." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/jzs.12201" volume="56" year="2018">Mammola et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Scopoli" baseAuthorityYear="1763" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Metellina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metellina merianae" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="429" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="merianae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="429">Metellina merianae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in Europe (
<bibRefCitation author="Nentwig, W" journalOrPublisher="Arthropoda Selecta, Supplement" pageId="0" pageNumber="429" publicationUrl="https://www.araneae.nmbe.ch" refId="B18" refString="Nentwig, W, Blick, T, Bosmans, R, Gloor, D, Haenggi, A, Kropf, C., 2020. Spiders of Europe. Version 09.2020. Online at https://www.araneae.nmbe.ch" title="Spiders of Europe. Version 09.2020. Online at" url="https://www.araneae.nmbe.ch" year="2020">Nentwig et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
) and is reported east to Urals (
<bibRefCitation author="Mikhailov, KG" journalOrPublisher="Arthropoda Selecta, Supplement" pageId="0" pageNumber="429" pagination="1 - 262" refId="B17" refString="Mikhailov, KG, 2013. The spiders (Arachnida: Aranei) of Russia and adjacent countries: a non-annotated checklist. Arthropoda Selecta, Supplement 3: 1 - 262" title="The spiders (Arachnida: Aranei) of Russia and adjacent countries: a non-annotated checklist." volume="3" year="2013">Mikhailov 2013</bibRefCitation>
) and the Altai Mountains (
<bibRefCitation author="Levina, NV" journalOrPublisher="Otdel biologicheskyi" pageId="0" pageNumber="429" pagination="38 - 52" refId="B10" refString="Levina, NV, Mikhailov, KG, 2004. Spider (Aranei) fauna of mountainous Altai. Bulleten' Moskowskogo Obshchestva Ispytatelei Prirody. Otdel biologicheskyi 109 (3): 38 - 52" title="Spider (Aranei) fauna of mountainous Altai. Bulleten' Moskowskogo Obshchestva Ispytatelei Prirody." volume="109" year="2004">Levina and Mikhailov 2004</bibRefCitation>
). It was reported from the caves of Iran, the Caucasus, the Crimea, the Russian Plain and the Urals (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/09397140.2014.943465" author="Marusik, YM" journalOrPublisher="Zoology in the Middle East" pageId="0" pageNumber="429" pagination="255 - 266" refId="B16" refString="Marusik, YM, Nadimi, A, Omelko, MM, Koponen, S, 2014. First data about cave spiders (Arachnida: Araneae) from Iran. Zoology in the Middle East 60 (3): 255 - 266, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/09397140.2014.943465" title="First data about cave spiders (Arachnida: Araneae) from Iran." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/09397140.2014.943465" volume="60" year="2014">Marusik et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Turbanov, IS" journalOrPublisher="Zoologicheskyi Zhurnal" pageId="0" pageNumber="429" pagination="1283 - 1304" refId="B22" refString="Turbanov, IS, Palatov, DM, Golovatch, SI, 2016. Current state of biospeleology in Russia and in countries of the former Soviet Union: the review of the invertebrate cave (endogeic) fauna. 2. Arachnida - Acknowledgements. Zoologicheskyi Zhurnal 95 (11): 1283 - 1304" title="Current state of biospeleology in Russia and in countries of the former Soviet Union: the review of the invertebrate cave (endogeic) fauna. 2. Arachnida - Acknowledgements." volume="95" year="2016">Turbanov et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). Outside the caves, this species occurs in the shaded habitats with boulders, along the creeks and in the cellars (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/09397140.2014.943465" author="Marusik, YM" journalOrPublisher="Zoology in the Middle East" pageId="0" pageNumber="429" pagination="255 - 266" refId="B16" refString="Marusik, YM, Nadimi, A, Omelko, MM, Koponen, S, 2014. First data about cave spiders (Arachnida: Araneae) from Iran. Zoology in the Middle East 60 (3): 255 - 266, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/09397140.2014.943465" title="First data about cave spiders (Arachnida: Araneae) from Iran." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/09397140.2014.943465" volume="60" year="2014">Marusik et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
). In the northern part of the Altai Mountains it was collected along a swampy stream in a birch forest (
<bibRefCitation author="Levina, NV" journalOrPublisher="Otdel biologicheskyi" pageId="0" pageNumber="429" pagination="38 - 52" refId="B10" refString="Levina, NV, Mikhailov, KG, 2004. Spider (Aranei) fauna of mountainous Altai. Bulleten' Moskowskogo Obshchestva Ispytatelei Prirody. Otdel biologicheskyi 109 (3): 38 - 52" title="Spider (Aranei) fauna of mountainous Altai. Bulleten' Moskowskogo Obshchestva Ispytatelei Prirody." volume="109" year="2004">Levina and Mikhailov 2004</bibRefCitation>
). The species reported from the Novosibirsk Oblast (Barsukovskaya Cave) for the first time. Records in the Barsukovskaya and Gavrilovskaya II Caves represent the northeasternmost localities of its distribution range.
</paragraph>
